22constexpr char kFieldTrial[] = "WebRTC-Video-BalancedDegradationSettings";
23constexpr int kMinFps = 1;
24constexpr int kMaxFps = 100; // 100 means unlimited fps.

59bool IsValidConfig(
60 const BalancedDegradationSettings::CodecTypeSpecific& config) {
61 if (config.GetQpLow().has_value() != config.GetQpHigh().has_value()) {
62 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Neither or both thresholds should be set.";
63 return false;
64 }
65 if (config.GetQpLow().has_value() && config.GetQpHigh().has_value() &&
66 config.GetQpLow().value() >= config.GetQpHigh().value()) {
67 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Invalid threshold value, low >= high threshold.";
68 return false;
69 }
70 if (config.GetFps().has_value() && (config.GetFps().value() < kMinFps ||
71 config.GetFps().value() > kMaxFps)) {
72 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Unsupported fps setting, value ignored.";
73 return false;
74 }
75 return true;
76}
77
78bool IsValid(const BalancedDegradationSettings::CodecTypeSpecific& config1,
79 const BalancedDegradationSettings::CodecTypeSpecific& config2) {
80 bool both_or_none_set = ((config1.qp_low > 0) == (config2.qp_low > 0) &&
81 (config1.qp_high > 0) == (config2.qp_high > 0) &&
82 (config1.fps > 0) == (config2.fps > 0));
83 if (!both_or_none_set) {
84 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Invalid value, all/none should be set.";
85 return false;
86 }
87 if (config1.fps > 0 && config1.fps < config2.fps) {
88 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Invalid fps/pixel value provided.";
89 return false;
90 }
91 return true;
92}
93
94bool IsValid(const std::vector<BalancedDegradationSettings::Config>& configs) {
95 if (configs.size() <= 1) {
96 if (configs.size() == 1)
97 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Unsupported size, value ignored.";
98 return false;
99 }
100 for (const auto& config : configs) {
101 if (config.fps < kMinFps || config.fps > kMaxFps) {
102 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Unsupported fps setting, value ignored.";
103 return false;
104 }
105 }
106 int last_kbps = configs[0].kbps;
107 for (size_t i = 1; i < configs.size(); ++i) {
108 if (configs[i].kbps > 0) {
109 if (configs[i].kbps < last_kbps) {
110 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Invalid bitrate value provided.";
111 return false;
112 }
113 last_kbps = configs[i].kbps;
114 }
115 }
116 for (size_t i = 1; i < configs.size(); ++i) {
117 if (configs[i].pixels < configs[i - 1].pixels ||
118 configs[i].fps < configs[i - 1].fps) {
119 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Invalid fps/pixel value provided.";
120 return false;
121 }
122 if (!IsValid(configs[i].vp8, configs[i - 1].vp8) ||
123 !IsValid(configs[i].vp9, configs[i - 1].vp9) ||
124 !IsValid(configs[i].h264, configs[i - 1].h264) ||
125 !IsValid(configs[i].av1, configs[i - 1].av1) ||
126 !IsValid(configs[i].generic, configs[i - 1].generic)) {
127 return false;
128 }
129 }
130 for (const auto& config : configs) {
131 if (!IsValidConfig(config.vp8) || !IsValidConfig(config.vp9) ||
132 !IsValidConfig(config.h264) || !IsValidConfig(config.av1) ||
133 !IsValidConfig(config.generic)) {
134 return false;
135 }
136 }
137 return true;
138}
139
140std::vector<BalancedDegradationSettings::Config> GetValidOrDefault(
141 const std::vector<BalancedDegradationSettings::Config>& configs) {
142 if (IsValid(configs)) {
143 return configs;
144 }
145 return DefaultConfigs();
146}
147
148absl::optional<VideoEncoder::QpThresholds> GetThresholds(
149 VideoCodecType type,
150 const BalancedDegradationSettings::Config& config) {
151 absl::optional<int> low;
152 absl::optional<int> high;
153
154 switch (type) {
155 case kVideoCodecVP8:
156 low = config.vp8.GetQpLow();
157 high = config.vp8.GetQpHigh();
158 break;
159 case kVideoCodecVP9:
160 low = config.vp9.GetQpLow();
161 high = config.vp9.GetQpHigh();
162 break;
163 case kVideoCodecH264:
164 low = config.h264.GetQpLow();
165 high = config.h264.GetQpHigh();
166 break;
167 case kVideoCodecAV1:
168 low = config.av1.GetQpLow();
169 high = config.av1.GetQpHigh();
170 break;
171 case kVideoCodecGeneric:
172 low = config.generic.GetQpLow();
173 high = config.generic.GetQpHigh();
174 break;
175 default:
176 break;
177 }
178
179 if (low && high) {
180 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "QP thresholds: low: " << *low << ", high: " << *high;
181 return absl::optional<VideoEncoder::QpThresholds>(
182 VideoEncoder::QpThresholds(*low, *high));
183 }
184 return absl::nullopt;
185}
186
187int GetFps(VideoCodecType type,
188 const absl::optional<BalancedDegradationSettings::Config>& config) {
189 if (!config.has_value()) {
190 return std::numeric_limits<int>::max();
191 }
192
193 absl::optional<int> fps;
194 switch (type) {
195 case kVideoCodecVP8:
196 fps = config->vp8.GetFps();
197 break;
198 case kVideoCodecVP9:
199 fps = config->vp9.GetFps();
200 break;
201 case kVideoCodecH264:
202 fps = config->h264.GetFps();
203 break;
204 case kVideoCodecAV1:
205 fps = config->av1.GetFps();
206 break;
207 case kVideoCodecGeneric:
208 fps = config->generic.GetFps();
209 break;
210 default:
211 break;
212 }
213
214 const int framerate = fps.value_or(config->fps);
215
216 return (framerate == kMaxFps) ? std::numeric_limits<int>::max() : framerate;
217}
218
219absl::optional<int> GetKbps(
220 VideoCodecType type,
221 const absl::optional<BalancedDegradationSettings::Config>& config) {
222 if (!config.has_value())
223 return absl::nullopt;
224
225 absl::optional<int> kbps;
226 switch (type) {
227 case kVideoCodecVP8:
228 kbps = config->vp8.GetKbps();
229 break;
230 case kVideoCodecVP9:
231 kbps = config->vp9.GetKbps();
232 break;
233 case kVideoCodecH264:
234 kbps = config->h264.GetKbps();
235 break;
236 case kVideoCodecAV1:
237 kbps = config->av1.GetKbps();
238 break;
239 case kVideoCodecGeneric:
240 kbps = config->generic.GetKbps();
241 break;
242 default:
243 break;
244 }
245
246 if (kbps.has_value())
247 return kbps;
248
249 return config->kbps > 0 ? absl::optional<int>(config->kbps) : absl::nullopt;
250}
251
252absl::optional<int> GetKbpsRes(
253 VideoCodecType type,
254 const absl::optional<BalancedDegradationSettings::Config>& config) {
255 if (!config.has_value())
256 return absl::nullopt;
257
258 absl::optional<int> kbps_res;
259 switch (type) {
260 case kVideoCodecVP8:
261 kbps_res = config->vp8.GetKbpsRes();
262 break;
263 case kVideoCodecVP9:
264 kbps_res = config->vp9.GetKbpsRes();
265 break;
266 case kVideoCodecH264:
267 kbps_res = config->h264.GetKbpsRes();
268 break;
269 case kVideoCodecAV1:
270 kbps_res = config->av1.GetKbpsRes();
271 break;
272 case kVideoCodecGeneric:
273 kbps_res = config->generic.GetKbpsRes();
274 break;
275 default:
276 break;
277 }
278
279 if (kbps_res.has_value())
280 return kbps_res;
281
282 return config->kbps_res > 0 ? absl::optional<int>(config->kbps_res)
283 : absl::nullopt;
284}

314BalancedDegradationSettings::Config::Config(int pixels,
315 int fps,
316 int kbps,
317 int kbps_res,
318 int fps_diff,
319 CodecTypeSpecific vp8,
320 CodecTypeSpecific vp9,
321 CodecTypeSpecific h264,
322 CodecTypeSpecific av1,
323 CodecTypeSpecific generic)
324 : pixels(pixels),
325 fps(fps),
326 kbps(kbps),
327 kbps_res(kbps_res),
328 fps_diff(fps_diff),
329 vp8(vp8),
330 vp9(vp9),
331 h264(h264),
332 av1(av1),
333 generic(generic) {}

335BalancedDegradationSettings::BalancedDegradationSettings() {
336 FieldTrialStructList<Config> configs(
337 {FieldTrialStructMember("pixels", [](Config* c) { return &c->pixels; }),
338 FieldTrialStructMember("fps", [](Config* c) { return &c->fps; }),
339 FieldTrialStructMember("kbps", [](Config* c) { return &c->kbps; }),
340 FieldTrialStructMember("kbps_res",
341 [](Config* c) { return &c->kbps_res; }),
342 FieldTrialStructMember("fps_diff",
343 [](Config* c) { return &c->fps_diff; }),
344 FieldTrialStructMember("vp8_qp_low",
345 [](Config* c) { return &c->vp8.qp_low; }),
346 FieldTrialStructMember("vp8_qp_high",
347 [](Config* c) { return &c->vp8.qp_high; }),
348 FieldTrialStructMember("vp8_fps", [](Config* c) { return &c->vp8.fps; }),
349 FieldTrialStructMember("vp8_kbps",
350 [](Config* c) { return &c->vp8.kbps; }),
351 FieldTrialStructMember("vp8_kbps_res",
352 [](Config* c) { return &c->vp8.kbps_res; }),
353 FieldTrialStructMember("vp9_qp_low",
354 [](Config* c) { return &c->vp9.qp_low; }),
355 FieldTrialStructMember("vp9_qp_high",
356 [](Config* c) { return &c->vp9.qp_high; }),
357 FieldTrialStructMember("vp9_fps", [](Config* c) { return &c->vp9.fps; }),
358 FieldTrialStructMember("vp9_kbps",
359 [](Config* c) { return &c->vp9.kbps; }),
360 FieldTrialStructMember("vp9_kbps_res",
361 [](Config* c) { return &c->vp9.kbps_res; }),
362 FieldTrialStructMember("h264_qp_low",
363 [](Config* c) { return &c->h264.qp_low; }),
364 FieldTrialStructMember("h264_qp_high",
365 [](Config* c) { return &c->h264.qp_high; }),
366 FieldTrialStructMember("h264_fps",
367 [](Config* c) { return &c->h264.fps; }),
368 FieldTrialStructMember("h264_kbps",
369 [](Config* c) { return &c->h264.kbps; }),
370 FieldTrialStructMember("h264_kbps_res",
371 [](Config* c) { return &c->h264.kbps_res; }),
372 FieldTrialStructMember("av1_qp_low",
373 [](Config* c) { return &c->av1.qp_low; }),
374 FieldTrialStructMember("av1_qp_high",
375 [](Config* c) { return &c->av1.qp_high; }),
376 FieldTrialStructMember("av1_fps", [](Config* c) { return &c->av1.fps; }),
377 FieldTrialStructMember("av1_kbps",
378 [](Config* c) { return &c->av1.kbps; }),
379 FieldTrialStructMember("av1_kbps_res",
380 [](Config* c) { return &c->av1.kbps_res; }),
381 FieldTrialStructMember("generic_qp_low",
382 [](Config* c) { return &c->generic.qp_low; }),
383 FieldTrialStructMember("generic_qp_high",
384 [](Config* c) { return &c->generic.qp_high; }),
385 FieldTrialStructMember("generic_fps",
386 [](Config* c) { return &c->generic.fps; }),
387 FieldTrialStructMember("generic_kbps",
388 [](Config* c) { return &c->generic.kbps; }),
389 FieldTrialStructMember("generic_kbps_res",
390 [](Config* c) { return &c->generic.kbps_res; })},
391 {});
392
393 ParseFieldTrial({&configs}, field_trial::FindFullName(kFieldTrial));
394
395 configs_ = GetValidOrDefault(configs.Get());
396 RTC_DCHECK_GT(configs_.size(), 1);
397}

403 return configs_;

406int BalancedDegradationSettings::MinFps(VideoCodecType type, int pixels) const {
407 return GetFps(type, GetMinFpsConfig(pixels));
408}
409
410absl::optional<BalancedDegradationSettings::Config>
411BalancedDegradationSettings::GetMinFpsConfig(int pixels) const {
412 for (const auto& config : configs_) {
413 if (pixels <= config.pixels)
414 return config;
415 }
416 return absl::nullopt;
417}
418
419int BalancedDegradationSettings::MaxFps(VideoCodecType type, int pixels) const {
420 return GetFps(type, GetMaxFpsConfig(pixels));
421}
422
423absl::optional<BalancedDegradationSettings::Config>
424BalancedDegradationSettings::GetMaxFpsConfig(int pixels) const {
425 for (size_t i = 0; i < configs_.size() - 1; ++i) {
426 if (pixels <= configs_[i].pixels)
427 return configs_[i + 1];
428 }
429 return absl::nullopt;
430}
431
432bool BalancedDegradationSettings::CanAdaptUp(VideoCodecType type,
433 int pixels,
434 uint32_t bitrate_bps) const {
435 absl::optional<int> min_kbps = GetKbps(type, GetMaxFpsConfig(pixels));
436 if (!min_kbps.has_value() || bitrate_bps == 0) {
437 return true; // No limit configured or bitrate provided.
438 }
439 return bitrate_bps >= static_cast<uint32_t>(min_kbps.value() * 1000);
440}
441
442bool BalancedDegradationSettings::CanAdaptUpResolution(
443 VideoCodecType type,
444 int pixels,
445 uint32_t bitrate_bps) const {
446 absl::optional<int> min_kbps = GetKbpsRes(type, GetMaxFpsConfig(pixels));
447 if (!min_kbps.has_value() || bitrate_bps == 0) {
448 return true; // No limit configured or bitrate provided.
449 }
450 return bitrate_bps >= static_cast<uint32_t>(min_kbps.value() * 1000);
451}
452
453absl::optional<int> BalancedDegradationSettings::MinFpsDiff(int pixels) const {
454 for (const auto& config : configs_) {
455 if (pixels <= config.pixels) {
456 return (config.fps_diff > kNoFpsDiff)
457 ? absl::optional<int>(config.fps_diff)
458 : absl::nullopt;
459 }
460 }
461 return absl::nullopt;
462}
463
464absl::optional<VideoEncoder::QpThresholds>
465BalancedDegradationSettings::GetQpThresholds(VideoCodecType type,
466 int pixels) const {
467 return GetThresholds(type, GetConfig(pixels));
468}
469
470BalancedDegradationSettings::Config BalancedDegradationSettings::GetConfig(
471 int pixels) const {
472 for (const auto& config : configs_) {
473 if (pixels <= config.pixels)
474 return config;
475 }
476 return configs_.back(); // Use last above highest pixels.
477}
